Name: zlib
Short Name: zlib
URL: http://zlib.net/
Revision: 1.2.11
License: zlib
License File: LICENSE
Security Critical: yes

Description:
“A massively spiffy yet delicately unobtrusive compression library.”

zlib is a free, general-purpose, legally unencumbered lossless data-compression
library. zlib implements the “deflate” compression algorithm described by RFC
1951, which combines the LZ77 (Lempel-Ziv) algorithm with Huffman coding. zlib
also implements the zlib (RFC 1950) and gzip (RFC 1952) wrapper formats.

Local Modifications:
With one exception, the files in the zlib directory are untouched, although only
source files from the zlib distribution are included. zconf.h has been modified
to #include "../names.h" to rename all zlib names with a CP_z_ prefix.
